134. Gas Station
Medium

One way pass
big O N

Important point is to prove if totalGas > totalCost, there must be a successful way. (unique)
Prove by contradiction.

class Solution {
    public int canCompleteCircuit(int[] gas, int[] cost) {
        int totalGas = 0;
        int totalCost = 0;
        int tankGas = 0;
        int start = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < gas.length; i++) {
            tankGas += gas[i];
            if (tankGas >= cost[i]) {
                tankGas -= cost[i];
            } else {
                start = i + 1;
                tankGas = 0;
            }
            totalGas += gas[i];
            totalCost += cost[i];
        }
        if (totalGas < totalCost) return -1;
        return start;
    }
}
